### Configure External Identities with GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

To use external identities (AWS, Azure, OIDC) with Application Default Credentials, generate a JSON credentials configuration file for your external identity. Store the path to this file in the GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS environment variable. The library will then automatically select the appropriate client and initialize credentials.

```bash
export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/config.json
```

