### Using External Identities with Application Default Credentials

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

Configure Application Default Credentials (ADC) to use external identities (AWS, Azure, OIDC) by generating a JSON credentials configuration file and setting the `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` environment variable.

```APIDOC
## Using External Identities with ADC

### Description
Integrate external identities such as AWS, Azure, or OIDC-based providers with Application Default Credentials (ADC). This involves generating a JSON configuration file for your external identity and setting the `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` environment variable to point to this file.

### Method
Environment Variable Configuration & Library Initialization

### Endpoint
N/A

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
None

### Request Example
**Environment Setup:**
```bash
export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/config.json
```

**Node.js Initialization:**
```js
const { GoogleAuth } = require('google-auth-library');

const auth = new GoogleAuth({
  scopes: 'https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform'
});

async function listBuckets() {
  const projectId = await auth.getProjectId();
  const url = `https://storage.googleapis.com/storage/v1/b?project=${projectId}`;
  // Assuming 'client' is an authenticated HTTP client instance
  // const res = await client.fetch(url);
  // console.log(res.data);
  console.log(`Project ID: ${projectId}`);
  console.log(`Storage API URL: ${url}`);
}

listBuckets().catch(console.error);
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
N/A (This section describes configuration, not a direct API response)

#### Response Example
N/A
```

