### Executable-Sourced Credentials with OIDC and SAML

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

Configuration for using executable-sourced credentials, where a local executable provides OIDC ID tokens or SAML assertions to stdout.

```APIDOC
## Executable-Sourced Credentials

### Description
Supports authentication using credentials provided by a local executable. The executable must output a valid OIDC ID token or SAML assertion in JSON format to standard output.

### Method
N/A (Environment Variable and Executable Execution)

### Endpoint
N/A

### Parameters
#### Environment Variables
- **GOOGLE_EXTERNAL_ACCOUNT_ALLOW_EXECUTABLES** (string) - Required - Must be set to `1` to enable executable-sourced credentials.

### Request Example
To generate an executable-sourced workload identity configuration, ensure the `GOOGLE_EXTERNAL_ACCOUNT_ALLOW_EXECUTABLES` environment variable is set to `1` and then execute the relevant command to set up the credentials. The exact command for generating the configuration is not fully provided in the input, but it would typically involve commands to set up the executable and its output.

### Response
#### Success Response
N/A (This setup relies on an external executable providing credentials.)

#### Response Example
N/A
```

