### Configure Executable-Sourced Credentials (Bash)

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

This command is used in conjunction with executable-sourced credentials. A local executable will be used to retrieve the 3rd party token and output it to stdout in JSON format. The GOOGLE_EXTERNAL_ACCOUNT_ALLOW_EXECUTABLES environment variable must be set to '1' for this to work.

```bash
# Set the environment variable to allow executables
export GOOGLE_EXTERNAL_ACCOUNT_ALLOW_EXECUTABLES=1

# Generate an executable-sourced workload identity configuration (command to be run by the executable itself)
# The executable should output the token in JSON format to stdout.
# Example placeholder command:
# your_token_generator_executable --audience "$AUDIENCE" --subject-token-type "$SUBJECT_TOKEN_TYPE"
```

