### Generate OIDC Credential Config using URL Source

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

Generates an OIDC configuration file for URL-sourced credentials. This command requires substituting placeholder variables with specific IDs, URLs, and headers. The output is a JSON file containing the configuration.

```bash
gcloud iam workforce-pools create-cred-config \
    locations/global/workforcePools/$WORKFORCE_POOL_ID/providers/$PROVIDER_ID \
    --subject-token-type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:token-type:id_token \
    --credential-source-url=$URL_TO_RETURN_OIDC_ID_TOKEN \
    --credential-source-headers $HEADER_KEY=$HEADER_VALUE \
    --workforce-pool-user-project=$WORKFORCE_POOL_USER_PROJECT \
    --output-file=/path/to/generated/config.json
```

