### External Account Authorized User Workforce Credentials

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

Instructions for generating and using external account authorized user workforce identity configurations, which allow sign-in via a web browser to an external identity provider.

```APIDOC
## External Account Authorized User Workforce Credentials

### Description
Enables authentication using external identity provider accounts by signing in through a web browser. A configuration is generated for the auth library to use, leveraging a refresh token to obtain access tokens.

### Method
`gcloud auth application-default login`

### Endpoint
N/A (CLI command)

### Parameters
#### Command Line Arguments
- **--login-config** (string) - Required - Path to the login configuration file.

### Request Example
```bash
gcloud auth application-default login --login-config=$LOGIN_CONFIG
```

Where `$LOGIN_CONFIG` is the path to a login configuration file, which can be generated via the Google Cloud Console or using `gcloud iam workforce-pools create-login-config`.

### Response
#### Success Response
The command configures Application Default Credentials (ADC) at the well-known location, storing an external account authorized user configuration.

#### Response Example
N/A (CLI output indicating successful configuration)
```

