### Generate Credential Config using gcloud CLI

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

This command generates a configuration file for executable-sourced credentials. It requires the workforce pool ID, provider ID, subject token type, the executable command with its path and arguments, the user project, and an output file path. Optional parameters include the executable timeout and output file for caching.

```bash
gcloud iam workforce-pools create-cred-config \
    locations/global/workforcePools/$WORKFORCE_POOL_ID/providers/$PROVIDER_ID \
    --subject-token-type=$SUBJECT_TOKEN_TYPE \
    --executable-command=$EXECUTABLE_COMMAND \
    --workforce-pool-user-project=$WORKFORCE_POOL_USER_PROJECT \
    --output-file /path/to/generated/config.json
```

