### Get Authenticated Client with Application Default Credentials (ADC) - Node.js

Source: https://context7.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/llms.txt

This snippet demonstrates how to create a GoogleAuth instance and obtain an authenticated client using Application Default Credentials (ADC). ADC automatically discovers credentials from the environment, simplifying authentication. It requires the 'google-auth-library' package and makes an authenticated request to a Google API.

```javascript
const {GoogleAuth} = require('google-auth-library');

async function main() {
  // Create GoogleAuth instance with required scopes
  const auth = new GoogleAuth({
    scopes: 'https://www.googleapis.com/auth/cloud-platform'
  });

  try {
    // Get authenticated client (auto-discovers credentials)
    const client = await auth.getClient();

    // Get project ID from environment
    const projectId = await auth.getProjectId();

    // Make authenticated request to Google API
    const url = `https://dns.googleapis.com/dns/v1/projects/${projectId}`;
    const res = await client.fetch(url);

    console.log('DNS Info:', res.data);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Authentication failed:', error.message);
  }
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

