### Generate X.509 Credential Config (Custom Location)

Source: https://github.com/googleapis/google-auth-library-nodejs/blob/main/README.md

This command generates X.509 certificate-sourced credential configuration files, specifying a custom location for the certificate configuration file. It requires project number, pool ID, provider ID, service account email, and paths to the certificate, private key, and trust chain, along with a custom path for the certificate configuration file.

```bash
gcloud iam workload-identity-pools create-cred-config \
    projects/$PROJECT_NUMBER/locations/global/workloadIdentityPools/$POOL_ID/providers/$PROVIDER_ID \
    --service-account $SERVICE_ACCOUNT_EMAIL \
    --credential-cert-path "$PATH_TO_CERTIFICATE" \
    --credential-cert-private-key-path "$PATH_TO_PRIVATE_KEY" \
    --credential-cert-trust-chain-path "$PATH_TO_TRUST_CHAIN" \
    --credential-cert-configuration-output-file "/custom/path/cert_config.json" \
    --output-file /path/to/config.json
```

